By: Hugh of Saint-Victor
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Nothing Real Is Lost
---
He is not solitary with whom is God, nor is the power of joy extinguished
because his appetite is kept from things abject and vile. He rather does
himself an injustice who admits to the society of his joy what is disgraceful
or unworthy of his love.
